It was low tide. The waves of the Antacean Sea lapped at the sands below the cliffs of Monqiz.

LineNo: 10291977,

Narrator: A trail was carved into the cliffsi...
en


A trail was carved into the cliffside, just wide enough for a single horse. Vina picked up speed as she guided her mare, Lizzie, around a sharp curve.

Player_Romus: Vina! Slow down!
en


"Vina! Slow down!"

LineNo: 10292197,

Player_Romus_Italic: I urged my own horse on. She balked...
en


I urged my own horse on. She balked at the steep drop, slowing us down.

LineNo: 10292203,

Player_Romus_Italic: I urged my own horse on. She balked...
Menu Text en


Go faster yourself.

LineNo: 10292305,

en


She glanced back at me for just long enough to roll her eyes.

en


"Meet you at the beach!"

en


Vina glanced back at me with a grin.

LineNo: 10292611,

Narrator: I watched her fly down the trail.
en


I watched her fly down the trail.

LineNo: 10292713,

Narrator: At the bottom of the trail was a sh...
en


At the bottom of the trail was a sheltered cove where Pabel had laid out a picnic lunch. I dismounted and sat down next to Vina.

LineNo: 10292815,

Player_Romus: Faster! Remember what I taught you!
en


"Faster! Remember what I taught you!"

LineNo: 10292923,

Narrator: She glanced back at me with a grin...
en


She glanced back at me with a grin and gave the horse a swift kick in the side with her spurred boot.

LineNo: 10293025,

Vina Toras: You really didn't have to come bac...
en


"You really didn't have to come back to Monqiz with me, Father."

LineNo: 10293143,

Player_Romus: I wanted to. It's been ages since...
en


"I wanted to. It's been ages since we had time together."

LineNo: 10293245,

Player_Romus: I'm grateful for the break. It's t...
en


"I'm grateful for the break. It's too hectic in Porte Drazon."

LineNo: 10293347,

Vina Toras: We could be spending time at Palas...
en


"We could be spending time at Palas Rezna. If you'd let me on the council, that is."

LineNo: 10293743,

Player_Romus: I wanted to. Council meetings don'...
en


"I wanted to. Council meetings don't exactly count as quality time together."

LineNo: 10293845,

Vina Toras: Deciding the fate of the country t...
en


"Deciding the fate of the country together? That screams quality time to me."

LineNo: 10294059,

Vina Toras: I like the pace. But I can't let L...
en


"I like the pace. But I can't let Lizzie think I've forgotten about her."

LineNo: 10294439,

Vina Toras: A Sordish resort in Monqiz! I can'...
en


"A Sordish resort in Monqiz! I can't believe you agreed to that."

LineNo: 10294565,

Vina Toras: Ah. I knew there was another reaso...
en


"Ah. I knew there was another reason."

LineNo: 10294667,

Narrator: She picked up a lobster salad sandw...
en


She picked up a lobster salad sandwich from the picnic basket and nibbled at it. A solemn silence descended as we stared out at the waves.

LineNo: 10294769,

Vina Toras: Eight years since she died. When I...
en


"Eight years since she died. When I'm here, it might as well have been yesterday."

LineNo: 10294895,

Vina Toras: I can't even dip my toe in the wat...
en


"I can't even dip my toe in the water, or it'll all come rushing back."

LineNo: 10294997,

Player_Romus: I'd still declare you next in line...
en


"I'd still declare you next in line. Rizia needs a queen like you, and the rules were meant to be broken."

LineNo: 10295099,

Player_Romus: He'd become my successor, of cours...
en


"He'd become my successor, of course. Those are the rules. But you'll still be a duchess."

LineNo: 10295471,

Player_Romus: You know what'll help blot out tho...
en


"You know what'll help blot out those memories? A big Sordish resort, right on this spot."

LineNo: 10295573,

Player_Romus: It'll get easier over time. It did...
en


"It'll get easier over time. It did for me."

LineNo: 10295675,

Player_Romus: Grief isn't a straight line, my da...
en


"Grief isn't a straight line, my daughter. It ebbs and flows like the tide."

LineNo: 10295777,

Vina Toras: It's always high tide for me. And...
en


"It's always high tide for me. And I'm not sure I even want to come up for air."

LineNo: 10295879,

Vina Toras: But you must be feeling the same w...
en


"But you must be feeling the same way about Mother. Otherwise, you would've remarried by now."

LineNo: 10295981,

Player_Romus: What makes you think Rizia will st...
en


"What makes you think Rizia will still be ruled by a monarch by the time I die?"

LineNo: 10296179,

Vina Toras: But you're a man. As long as your...
en


"But you're a man. As long as your wife's young enough, you could have another child at any age."

LineNo: 10296377,

Narrator: She folded her arms.
en


She folded her arms.

LineNo: 10296479,

Narrator: She smiled.
en


She smiled.

LineNo: 10296859,

Player_Romus: I've got to do some glad-handing h...
en


"I've got to do some glad-handing here anyway, before the Sordish invasion begins."

LineNo: 10296961,

Player_Romus: I just wanted to relish the sight...
en


"I just wanted to relish the sight of this beautiful, Sord-free beach."

Vina Toras: A Sordish resort in Monqiz! I can'...
en


"A Sordish resort in Monqiz! I can't believe they thought you'd go for it."

Vina Toras: Don't you think that's a little el...
en


"Don't you think that's a little elitist? Beaches should belong to everyone."

Player_Romus: You don't have anything to worry a...
en


"You don't have anything to worry about. My childbearing days are over."

LineNo: 10297957,

Narrator: She sighed.
en


She sighed.

LineNo: 10298059,

Vina Toras: Never mind.
en


"Never mind."

LineNo: 10298161,

Vina Toras: Like Queen Lyza said. The eldest s...
en


"Like Queen Lyza said. The eldest sibling should inherit the throne, no matter their sex."

LineNo: 10298263,

Narrator: The tide was beginning to lap at th...
en


The tide was beginning to lap at the edge of our blanket. We stood up and pulled it away from the water.

LineNo: 10298643,

Vina Toras: But... Queen Lyza always said the...
en


"But... Queen Lyza always said the eldest child should inherit the throne. No matter their sex."

LineNo: 10298745,

Vina Toras: Then let's see how many rules I ca...
en


"Then let's see how many rules I can break once I'm queen."

LineNo: 10298847,

Vina Toras: The rules are the rules, I get it....
en


"The rules are the rules, I get it. No use being queen if the people don't want me, anyway."

LineNo: 10298949,

Vina Toras: Never mind. Who knows if it will e...
en


"Never mind. Who knows if it will even happen."

LineNo: 10299051,

Vina Toras: Father? One more thing.
en


"Father? One more thing."

LineNo: 10299169,

Player_Romus: What?
en


"What?"

LineNo: 10299271,

Player_Romus: I'm not hungry right now. I'll eat...
en


"I'm not hungry right now. I'll eat my sandwich when we get back to the palace."

LineNo: 10299373,

Narrator: She hopped astride Lizzie.
en


She hopped astride Lizzie.

LineNo: 10299475,

Vina Toras: It's just...
en


"It's just..."

LineNo: 10299577,

Vina Toras: No, not that.
en


"No, not that."

LineNo: 10299679,

Vina Toras: Grandmother is always on about how...
en


"Grandmother is always on about how I need to find the right husband."

LineNo: 10299781,

Vina Toras: How important is it to you, really...
en


"How important is it to you, really? Whom I marry?"

LineNo: 10299907,

Player_Romus: Why? Do you have any candidates in...
en


"Why? Do you have any candidates in mind?"

LineNo: 10300009,

Player_Romus: Don't listen to that hypocrite. Gr...
en


"Don't listen to that hypocrite. Grandma followed her heart, and so should you."

LineNo: 10300111,

Vina Toras: No, but do *you*? Are you going to...
en


"No, but do *you*? Are you going to marry me off, like your father did to you?"

LineNo: 10300229,

Player_Romus: I don't care whom you marry. As lo...
en


"I don't care whom you marry. As long as he's of noble birth, of course."

LineNo: 10300331,

Player_Romus: You're a princess, Vina. Your marr...
en


"You're a princess, Vina. Your marriage status matters not only to me, but to the whole country."

LineNo: 10300433,

Vina Toras: Does that mean you're planning to...
en


"Does that mean you're planning to marry me off? Like your father did to you?"

LineNo: 10300559,

Vina Toras: So you're not planning to marry me...
en


"So you're not planning to marry me off. Like your father did to you."

LineNo: 10300677,

Player_Romus: I'm still considering all the opti...
en


"I'm still considering all the options."

LineNo: 10300779,

Player_Romus: My arranged marriage was the best...
en


"My arranged marriage was the best thing that ever happened to me."

LineNo: 10300881,

Player_Romus: Absolutely not. Arranged marriage...
en


"Absolutely not. Arranged marriage is a barbaric tradition."

LineNo: 10301261,

Vina Toras: I wasn't blind and deaf growing up...
en


"I wasn't blind and deaf growing up. I don't want to end up like you and Mother."

LineNo: 10301387,

Vina Toras: You and Mother were lucky to fall...
en


"You and Mother were lucky to fall in love. Most such marriages are miserable."

LineNo: 10301513,

Player_Romus: I might suggest a potential husban...
en


"I might suggest a potential husband or two. But I'll never drag you to the altar."

LineNo: 10301615,

Player_Romus: And what if I am?
en


"And what if I am?"

LineNo: 10301717,

Vina Toras: You and Mother were living proof o...
en


"You and Mother were living proof of that."

LineNo: 10302113,

Vina Toras: It worked out for you and Mother.
en


"It worked out for you and Mother."

LineNo: 10302231,

Narrator: She fixed me with a stare.
en


She fixed me with a stare.

LineNo: 10302333,

Player_Romus: You want to be queen? This is part...
en


"You want to be queen? This is part of it. A single wedding can accomplish more than a hundred political conferences."

LineNo: 10302435,

Player_Romus: Relax. I might suggest a potential...
en


"Relax. I might suggest a potential husband or two, but I'll never drag you to the altar."

LineNo: 10302537,

Player_Romus: Whether or not I loved her, I did...
en


"Whether or not I loved her, I did what I was ordered to do. As you will when the day comes."

LineNo: 10302639,

Vina Toras: So you won't try to marry me off....
en


"So you won't try to marry me off. Like your father did to you."

LineNo: 10302853,

Player_Romus: Think of it as yet another one of...
en


"Think of it as yet another one of your royal obligations. You can always take a lover on the side."

LineNo: 10302955,

Player_Romus: I trust you to make the right deci...
en


"I trust you to make the right decision. For yourself, and for Rizia."

Narrator: She regarded me coolly for a moment...
en


She regarded me coolly for a moment.

LineNo: 10303437,

Narrator: She mulled over my words for a mome...
en


She mulled over my words for a moment.

LineNo: 10303635,

Narrator: She looked relieved.
en


She looked relieved.

LineNo: 10303737,

Vina Toras: I'm interested in hearing these su...
en


"I'm interested in hearing these suggestions."

LineNo: 10303839,

Vina Toras: That's the least I could ask of yo...
en


"That's the least I could ask of you. But good to know."

LineNo: 10304219,

Player_Romus: We were an exception.
en


"We were an exception."

LineNo: 10304321,

Narrator: She smiled.
en


She smiled.

LineNo: 10304423,

Narrator: Her expression was hard to read.
en


Her expression was hard to read.

LineNo: 10304803,

Vina Toras: Let's hope that my heart and Rizia...
en


"Let's hope that my heart and Rizia's needs align."

Vina Toras: I appreciate your honesty. I do kn...
en


"I appreciate your honesty. I do know we royals must make compromises in our personal lives."

LineNo: 10305007,

Player_Romus: We both loved you. And we both swo...
en


"We both loved you. And we both swore you'd never go through the same hell we did."

LineNo: 10305109,

Player_Romus: I don't know what you're talking a...
en


"I don't know what you're talking about."

LineNo: 10305211,

Player_Romus: All because I didn't have the cour...
en


"All because I didn't have the courage to speak to my father as an equal. You're braver than I was."

LineNo: 10305313,

Player_Romus: We made the best of the situation...
en


"We made the best of the situation we'd been forced into."

LineNo: 10305415,

Player_Romus: I still wish I'd had a choice. The...
en


"I still wish I'd had a choice. The least I can do is grant you one."

LineNo: 10305517,

Narrator: She nodded.
en


She nodded.

LineNo: 10305715,

Vina Toras: That means a lot, Father. And it's...
en


"That means a lot, Father. And it's a decision I won't take lightly."

LineNo: 10305817,

Narrator: She regarded me coolly for a second...
en


She regarded me coolly for a second.

LineNo: 10305919,

Vina Toras: I wasn't deaf or blind as a child,...
en


"I wasn't deaf or blind as a child, you know. I'm happy I won't have to subject my own to the same fate."

LineNo: 10306021,

Vina Toras: I hope someday I can have what you...
en


"I hope someday I can have what you two had. Arranged or otherwise."

Narrator: I staggered through the doorway of...
en


I staggered through the doorway of Palas Monqiz, exhausted. Pabel swiftly took my coat.

LineNo: 10306503,

Pabel Adria: Welcome back, Your Majesty.
en


"Welcome back, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10306605,

Player_Romus: She's too fast for her old man.
en


"She's too fast for her old man."

LineNo: 10306707,

Player_Romus: She's visiting with a friend, but...
en


"She's visiting with a friend, but she wanted to thank you for lunch."

Player_Romus: In another castle. I let her go ou...
en


"In another castle. I let her go out, against my better judgement."

Pabel Adria: I remember a certain Romus Toras b...
en


"I remember a certain Romus Toras being quite the rider himself."

Pabel Adria: I heard you used to be quite the r...
en


"I heard you used to be quite the rider yourself."

Pabel Adria: Monqiz lobster. It's never so swee...
en


"Monqiz lobster. It's never so sweet as when it's fresh out of the water."

LineNo: 10307495,

Pabel Adria: She's more than old enough to go o...
en


"She's more than old enough to go out alone. You can't protect her from everything."

Pabel Adria: Any daughter of King Romus is boun...
en


"Any daughter of King Romus is bound to have a strong will."

LineNo: 10307699,

Player_Romus: You read my mind, Pabel.
en


"You read my mind, Pabel."

Player_Romus: I'm not sore at all. But a bath so...
en


"I'm not sore at all. But a bath sounds good."

LineNo: 10307903,

Player_Romus: Only if it's got bubbles.
en


"Only if it's got bubbles."

LineNo: 10308005,

Pabel Adria: All part of the job.
en


"All part of the job."

LineNo: 10308107,

Pabel Adria: Let me know if you need anything e...
en


"Let me know if you need anything else."

LineNo: 10308209,

Pabel Adria: Is there any other kind of bath?
en


"Is there any other kind of bath?"

Narrator: I made my way to Palas Monqiz's mas...
en


I made my way to Palas Monqiz's master bathroom, where an enormous clawfoot tub was filled to the brim with soapy, eucalyptus-scented water. I undressed and got in.

LineNo: 10308437,

Player_Romus_Italic: I scrubbed my right arm. The temper...
en


I scrubbed my right arm. The temperature was perfect.

Menu Text en


Scrub your right arm.

en


I scrubbed my left arm. The temperature was perfect.

Player_Romus_Italic: I scrubbed my left arm. The tempera...
Menu Text en


Scrub your left arm.

en


I scrubbed my right leg. The temperature was perfect.

Menu Text en


Scrub your right leg.

en


I scrubbed my left leg. The temperature was perfect.

Scrub your left leg.

en


A tap came at the door, so soft I thought I was imagining it at first.

Pabel Adria: Your Majesty?
en


"Your Majesty?"

LineNo: 10309359,

Pabel Adria: Romus?
en


"Romus?"

Player_Romus: Not now. Go away.
en


"Not now. Go away."

LineNo: 10309571,

Player_Romus: Yes?
en


"Yes?"

Pabel Adria: I'll just be a second. I forgot to...
en


"I'll just be a second. I forgot to leave you a towel."

LineNo: 10309791,

Player_Romus: All right. Come in.
en


"All right. Come in."

LineNo: 10309893,

Player_Romus: Don't you have anything better to...
en


"Don't you have anything better to do? Stop bothering me."

LineNo: 10309995,

Pabel Adria: Very well. Have a nice bath, Your...
en


"Very well. Have a nice bath, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10310471,

Pabel Adria: Very well. Have a nice bath.
en


"Very well. Have a nice bath."

LineNo: 10310573,

Narrator: After a thorough soak, I dressed an...
en


After a thorough soak, I dressed and headed to my study. I still had some work to go over before the trip back.

LineNo: 10310675,

Narrator: I heard his footsteps receding in t...
en


I heard his footsteps receding in the hallway.

LineNo: 10310777,

Narrator: She smiled.
en


She smiled.

LineNo: 10310879,

Narrator: She seemed to shrink a little.
en


She seemed to shrink a little.

LineNo: 10310981,

Vina Toras: Whatever you say, Father. I should...
en


"Whatever you say, Father. I should be going now."

LineNo: 10311179,

Narrator: She'd thrown herself into horseback...
en


She'd thrown herself into horseback riding after Lena died. We kept a few horses in Porte Drazon as well, but Lizzie was her favorite.

LineNo: 10311281,

Narrator: I followed her at a leisurely pace,...
en


I followed her at a leisurely pace, taking time to gaze back up the hill at Palas Monqiz. With Hubertus Toras governing the province from his own estate, I was free to visit my old home and its private beach anytime I liked.

LineNo: 10311383,

Player_Romus: We already discussed this. What ha...
en


"We already discussed this. What have you been doing instead?"

LineNo: 10311485,

Player_Romus: I don't know how much we're decidi...
en


"I don't know how much we're deciding. Sometimes I feel like it's out of any of our hands."

LineNo: 10311587,

Player_Romus: My mother was right about a few th...
en


"My mother was right about a few things. It's not healthy to spend too long in those chambers."

LineNo: 10311689,

Player_Romus: Keep up that enthusiasm. It will s...
en


"Keep up that enthusiasm. It will serve you well when you're older."

LineNo: 10311791,

Vina Toras: The usual. Ballgoing. Public appea...
en


"The usual. Ballgoing. Public appearances. Grandmother enrolled me in an advanced etiquette class."

LineNo: 10311893,

Player_Romus: Not our beach, though, right?
en


"Not our beach, though, right?"

LineNo: 10311995,

Vina Toras: Why should we be an exception?
en


"Why should we be an exception?"

LineNo: 10312105,

Player_Romus: A Marcel Koronti resort on these s...
en


"A Marcel Koronti resort on these shores would attract the worst kind of elitist. Trust me."

LineNo: 10312207,

Vina Toras: You're probably right. I've read a...
en


"You're probably right. I've read about him and his horrible father."

LineNo: 10312325,

Player_Romus: Everyone in *Rizia*. The Sords hav...
en


"Everyone in *Rizia*. The Sords have their own beaches."

LineNo: 10312427,

Player_Romus: Trust me, it's nowhere near as exc...
en


"Trust me, it's nowhere near as exciting as you imagine."

LineNo: 10312529,

Vina Toras: I'm sure it's more exciting than t...
en


"I'm sure it's more exciting than the etiquette class Grandmother made me start taking."

LineNo: 10312631,

Player_Romus: None of your backtalk. Let's just...
en


"None of your backtalk. Let's just treasure what time we have."

LineNo: 10312733,

Vina Toras: Hectic for you, maybe. I'm bored t...
en


"Hectic for you, maybe. I'm bored to tears."

LineNo: 10313121,

Vina Toras: By the way, did you know it's cons...
en


"By the way, did you know it's considered polite to intentionally lose a Derdian Duel of Generosity?"

LineNo: 10313247,

Player_Romus: What would you have done?
en


"What would you have done?"

LineNo: 10313349,

Player_Romus: They made me drink whiskey. It wen...
en


"They made me drink whiskey. It went to my head."

LineNo: 10313451,

Player_Romus: Are you questioning my decision?
en


"Are you questioning my decision?"

LineNo: 10313553,

Narrator: She considered it seriously.
en


She considered it seriously.

LineNo: 10313655,

Vina Toras: Honestly... I probably would have...
en


"Honestly... I probably would have let them have it. Lyza knew how valuable it was to be close to Sordland."

LineNo: 10313757,

Player_Romus: It was the right diplomatic move....
en


"It was the right diplomatic move. I'm sure of it."

LineNo: 10313859,

Player_Romus: And what would you have done?
en


"And what would you have done?"

LineNo: 10313961,

Narrator: My daughter fell silent.
en


My daughter fell silent.

LineNo: 10314063,

Vina Toras: Not at all, Father. I'm sure you h...
en


"Not at all, Father. I'm sure you had your reasons."

Vina Toras: No need to make excuses, Father. A...
en


"No need to make excuses, Father. A King stands by his decisions."

LineNo: 10314267,

Vina Toras: I'll miss the unobstructed views,...
en


"I'll miss the unobstructed views, though."

LineNo: 10314369,

Player_Romus: I may have made the wrong diplomat...
en


"I may have made the wrong diplomatic move, but it felt right in my heart."

LineNo: 10314471,

Vina Toras: No need to make excuses, Father. A...
en


"No need to make excuses, Father. A King stands by his decisions."

LineNo: 10314573,

Player_Romus: They thought they could buy me wit...
en


"They thought they could buy me with their greasy Sordish ren. I showed them."

LineNo: 10314675,

Vina Toras: I'm sure you did, Father.
en


"I'm sure you did, Father."

LineNo: 10314777,

Narrator: I looked out at the sea again.
en


I looked out at the sea again.

LineNo: 10314887,

Narrator: But they were too strong.
en


But they were too strong.

LineNo: 10315267,

Player_Romus_Italic: The memories rushed over me.
en


The memories rushed over me.

LineNo: 10315273,

Player_Romus_Italic: The memories rushed over me.

Let yourself remember.

en


I consciously tried to repress my memories.

Player_Romus_Italic: I consciously tried to repress my m...
Menu Text en


Try not to think about it.

LineNo: 10315483,

Narrator: The sickening sound the boat had ma...
en


The sickening sound the boat had made as its girders splintered. Calling out for my wife, over and over, until my voice finally gave out. The beep of the hospital machines as I told Vina to say goodbye to her mother one last time.
